<br>
Just a oppinion from the pull group cleric here.<br>
<br>
I dont think the initial break in strategy was a problem. Well except one thing. The ENTIRE night should be 'Stand and Die'. The intial break in was get to camp and fight, regardless if you are aggroed. The stand and die was not in effect on the first try. Which was needed.<br>
<br>
But more importantly, I like the idea of the 4-5 break in groups and no more. (which is what ultimatly worked, or i think it was only 4)  That is 4-5 groups of very disciplined people. That last break in was actually alot of fun. For some reason I felt safe when we arrived at camp and started clearing wanderers. It was good to have somthing go right. It gave us a feeling of accomplishment.<br>
<br>
The more people or groups you throw in there the better chance there is of those small number of people training camp. The more people.. the bigger chance of aggro. <br>
<br>
It actually can be represented statistically. For the more people you put in thier the higher the percentage of mistakes their will be made. Remeber your chain is only as strong as the weakest link, very evident last night.<br>
<br>
How do we fix? Veterans. People with proven discipline, and a number of sucessful raids under thier belts. People who the leaders know can do the job right. And in turn themselves are leaders.<br>
<br>
<br>
anyways, I'll see you all laters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
