</font><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CBC6B1><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urezton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rezton</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>3/31/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>9:55:36 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Fear Recap.. 3/30</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">This could shed some light on last nights assisting problems... got this of the eq clerics board:<br>
<br>
------------------<br>
They changed assist last patch to target (and attack if you have that option on) your assist person's target, wether they are actually attacking or not. <br>
Personally, I think this is a huge pain in the ass, and I've noticed a large number of our chanters and clerics are taking some extra abuse because of it......<br>
------------------------<br>
<br>
So it looks like people should not hit that assist button until the main uses /shout to annouce what they are attacking. Otherwise the main could have gotten hit by a mob (automatically targeting said mob), then that mob is mezzed, and then changes to a mob that cannot be mezzed. Which is then the /shout target.<br>
<br>
Also, just a thought. Put your ATTACKONASSIST in your eqclient.ini to FALSE and then when you assist you wont auto attack. You then check your target... if you thing it may be wrong... assist the main again (/target rbecka /assist)<br>
<br>
With the ATTACKONASSIST to FALSE you have little to no chance of breaking mez. Only after you have sucessfully assisted the main.. you hit your auto attack key.<br>
<br>
but then again, how are you gonna explain that to 50 people 6 minutes before we zone in <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
just some thoughts....</font><P><font color = "#FF1c1c">
