</font><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urezton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rezton</A> at: 3/31/01 9:57:59 pm</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#FFFFCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>3/31/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#8E9173>11:40:47 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Fear Recap.. 3/30</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I just have one correction to make on the strategy. <br>
<br>
West wall breakins are not to use the entire raid. You only use 3-5 groups of experienced people you trust. You go in, have everything in those 3-5 groups hit one target, kill it and all groups evac at the same time. Regroup, med up, wait for the FD'ed person at the portal to say it's clear, zone in, kill another mob and evac. Keep doing this until the 12 or so portal wanderers are dead. No groups are to evac until the raid commander calls an evac, then they all go. If all groups are assisting on the same target, and the evacers don't get swamped, this should work out quickly and well. The more mobs you kill on each attempt in, the easier the next attempt will be. The idea is to clear the portal of wanderers and any extra mobs you might aggro, then once you feel safe at the west wall, zone the rest in one group at a time. <br>
<br>
What happens if you zone everyone in at the same time is that you have many Linkdeaths, and as Rez said, the more folks you get in there, the better chance that a mob or 20 will aggro on them, the camp will be trained and you have a wipeout. <br>
<br>
Haemish</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showMessage?topicID=131.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showMessage?topicID=70.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=129.topic&index=13><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.emailToFriend?topicID=129.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/images/email.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Email This To a Friend"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;Email This To a Friend</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.threadControl?topicID=129.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=129.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Subscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to receive email notification of replies</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=129.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Unsubscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</FONT><BR></TD><TD></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=3 ALIGN=CENTER><BR><FORM ACTION=http://pub6.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum METHOD=POST><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Jump to: </FONT><SELECT NA